en_160434_0	The police constable who shot at the UNP headquarters at Pitakotte with his service gun has been remanded today by the Nugegoda Magistrate until May 15th.
en_160434_1	Magistrate Kanishka Wijerathna further ordered the Superintendent of Welikada Prison to refer the suspect to Angoda Mental hospital and obtained a report on his mental condition.
en_160434_2	The suspect had shot at the name board which is installed at the entrance of UNP Headquarters Sirikotha and, damaged its elephant emblem yesterday.
en_160434_3	The 40-year old suspect was attached to the Mirihana police station and is a resident of Megahatenna, Mathugama.
